{
  "stem": "1363.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I have photos of her, too, funny enough, after so many years.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Anyway, these were nice times in Wunstorf.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then, as I said, that was already close to '38-- '37, '37, '36.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I had to go over for one year to my grandma, my paternal grandmother.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They lived in Bratislava, in [INAUDIBLE], with her daughter and her son-in-law.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I lived there for a year, which was very pleasant as well.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I didn't have none of my parents or my brother with me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was alone with my grandma sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can't remember exactly.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think my mother came back to Hungary with my brother, who wasn't-- he was healthy by that time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he was always somehow physically the weaker one out of the two.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And now with common sense, I think that the birth, after 14 months of the first child, me, who was a very healthy, strong girl, he suffered by my mother's not giving herself enough time between one and the second child.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she came back to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I stayed with Grandma.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Why, what was the background, I don't really know, never questioned it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I didn't see my father much after that, because after Bratislava, I came to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "None of the schools, again.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know, is that a [LAUGHS] block, a mental block against schools?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On the other hand, I remember when we got-- when I got back to Budapest, I couldn't speak any Hungarian at all.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They made me, more or less, forget French.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because I had to concentrate on German to be good in school in Wunstorf.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So automatically, my French was totally neglected.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
